<P>
FIRE DEPT. VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Re "Fire Chief Apologizes for Portrayal of Video," Dec. 14: 
</P>
<P>
 Rather than investigating whether Chief Donald Manning and the Los Angeles 
Fire Department were making a "blooper" tape or just trying to "cover their 
burros," Fire Commissioner Leslie Song Winner should be concerning herself with 
a far more serious problem. Winner, the entire Fire Commission and even The 
Times should be trying to find out if any of those physically inept persons, of 
whatever gender or ethnic persuasion, depicted in the infamous video have 
slipped through the drafty cracks of affirmative action and are now sitting in 
a fire station, an accident waiting to happen. 
</P>
<P>
 TERRENCE BEASOR 
</P>
