<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: CASITAS PLANTS TROUT, BUT BASS GET HARVESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nothing like a trout plant to improve the fishing -- for bass. 
</P>
<P>
 "We had a couple of trout plants in the past week and it really perked the 
bass up," spokeswoman Gwen Fraser said at Ventura County's Lake Casitas.  
</P>
<P>
 It did indeed. Paul Beppu of Ventura used an AC Plug, which sort of resembles 
a trout, to catch bass weighing 14 and nine pounds. Other big bass were an 11 
3/4-pounder caught by Charles Razo of Oxnard and an 11-pounder by Jim Mason of 
Oak View. 
</P>
</TEXT>
