<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; LAGUNA HILLS, EL TORO PLAY TO A TIE IN GIRLS' SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laguna Hills and El Toro each played one half of uninspired soccer in a 1-1 
tie Tuesday at Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers dominated the Hawks, who could not produce any offense in the 
first half. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro (3-3-3) kept the ball in Hawk territory for most of the first half. 
Thirty-six minutes into the game, senior Mandy Lashmett got the ball in front 
of the net and put it in the corner over goalkeeper Deborah Mundis' head. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second half, the tables turned as Laguna Hills (3-3-2) took control on 
offense. The Hawks allowed the Chargers only three shots and attempted nine on 
El Toro freshman goalkeeper Melody Derloshon. 
</P>
<P>
 Derloshon, who finished with four saves in one half, made two impressive 
diving saves before Laguna Hills forward Ashley Olivieri took a crossing pass 
from junior Carrie Geyer in front of the net and slammed it out Derloshon's 
reach with 25 minutes left to play. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
