<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: EVERSON RESIGNS, FIGURES TO BE NET LOSS FOR AGOURA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Everson, who coached Agoura High to consecutive Marmonte League girls' 
volleyball titles, has resigned to pursue coaching opportunities in Santa 
Barbara after being dissatisfied with the school's commitment to the volleyball 
program. 
</P>
<P>
 Everson, a walk-on coach, led the girls' volleyball team for two seasons and 
the boys' team in 1994. 
</P>
<P>
 The Chargers reached the second round of the Southern Section Division I 
playoffs last month before losing to Newport Harbor, the top-ranked team in the 
nation. 
</P>
<P>
 "I wanted to stay and get the team into position to compete at the state level 
but I felt there was a lack of support at the school," Everson said. MICHAEL 
LAZARUS 
</P>
</TEXT>
