<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; FATHER 
CONVICTED IN DEATH OF 3-MONTH-OLD DAUGHTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Los Angeles man was convicted of second-degree murder Tuesday in the death 
of his infant daughter, who he claimed was killed in retaliation for his 
testimony in a gang murder case.  
</P>
<P>
 Anthony Bullock, 21, slammed down his fist and lowered his head when the 
jury's verdict was read.Superior Court Judge Mary Ann Murphy scheduled 
sentencing for Jan. 31. Bullock faces a maximum of 15 years to life. 
</P>
<P>
 His 3-month-old daughter, Shantez, was killed Oct. 30, 1993. The baby suffered 
severe head injuries and may have been suffocated, Deputy Medical Examiner 
Eugene Carpenter testified during the trial. He said the baby's body showed 
signs of previous abuse. 
</P>
<P>
 A police report said Bullock told investigators that out of fear and anxiety, 
he had accidentally slammed her with considerable force into a wall. But during 
the trial, he testified that gang members had killed her. 
</P>
