<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Despite public perceptions that crime is on the increase, at least one of the 
most dreaded forms of street crime is actually on the decline. 
</P>
<P>
 Gas station and convenience store robberies in Orange County have decreased in 
recent years, according to the Department of Justice, Bureau of Criminal 
Statistics.Here's the trend: Today 
</P>
<P>
 This is the deadline to register for a Christmas dinner to be served Dec. 23 
at the Norman P. Murray Senior Center in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 The traditional holiday dinner will include turkey, stuffing and all the 
trimmings. The dining area will be decorated for the holidays. Music and 
entertainment will also be provided. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is at 24932 Oso Viejo Road in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
 To make a reservation or get more information, call (714) 470-3063. 
</P>
