<TEXT>
<P>
 San Bernardino County authorities Tuesday identified a man who died in a plane 
crash near Big Bear City as Dean Henry, 29, of Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
 Henry was the pilot of a single-engine 1947 North American Navion-A that 
crashed Monday into a hillside half a mile east of Big Bear Airport, according 
to the San Bernadino County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
 One passenger, who has not been identified, was also killed in the crash, 
while another passenger survived, but is hospitalized with serious injuries, a 
coroner's spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The aircraft went down just after takeoff about 2 p.m., authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cause of the crash has not been determined. MAKI BECKER 
