<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 10-YEAR-OLD BOY SHOOTS HIMSELF TO DEATH 
PLAYING WITH HANDGUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 10-year-old boy accidentally shot and killed himself Tuesday while playing 
with a handgun he found in an abandoned car, Los Angeles County sheriff's 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred at 2:15 p.m. in the 37800 block of 90th Street East as 
the boy played with a .38-caliber gun in the living room of his mother's 
trailer, according to Deputy Britta Tubbs.The boy, whose name was not released, 
died of a single gunshot wound to the head, Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy and his 12-year-old brother were visiting an aunt a few blocks from 
their home when the younger boy found the gun in an abandoned car outside his 
aunt's house and did not tell his brother, Tubbs said. When the boys returned 
home, the older brother left the 10-year-old alone while he used the bathroom. 
He heard a shot and ran into the living room, Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He found the other brother lying on the sofa . . . with the gun at his side," 
Tubbs said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said the boys may have been having problems with youths from a 
local park and the younger brother may have wanted the firearm as a form of 
protection. 
</P>
<P>
 Neighbors said the boys' mother was in shock. "The mother is taking it very 
badly. It is very hard for her," said Sarphine Phillips. "She said the boy 
found the gun under a car but it is all still a mystery." 
</P>
</TEXT>
