<HEADLINE>
<P>
AT LEAST EIGHT KILLED IN SOMALIA CLASHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Clans loyal to Mogadishu's rival warlords fought fierce street battles 
Tuesday, killing at least eight people and wounding more than 100.Most of the 
victims were civilians caught in cross-fire. 
</P>
<P>
 The fighting broke out late Monday, ending a week of relative calm with a 
barrage of mortars, grenades, heavy machine guns and small-arms fire. 
</P>
<P>
 Hospital officials said supplies were running out and appeals to aid agencies 
had gone unanswered. 
</P>
