<TEXT>
<P>
 Secret Russian cargo bulky enough to fill one of the world's largest airplanes 
has been delivered to the Redstone Arsenal, an Army base in Huntsville, 
Ala.Army officials admitted that truckloads of material were delivered by a 
Russian An-124 aircraft, but nobody would say what the cargo was. "This is 
classified," said Dave Harris, a civilian public information officer at the 
base. "I can tell you that it was not nuclear material and that there was 
nothing on that plane that poses a hazard." 
