</P>
<P>
 In the meantime, Perry can continue playing for the Raiders, who finish the 
regular season Saturday, but hope to qualify for postseason play.  
</P>
<P>
 Two Raider teammates in the car at the time of the incident were not charged. 
The district attorney's office declined to identify them.  
</P>
<P>
 Raider official Al LoCasale said he had no knowledge of the incident. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-6, 305-pound Perry practiced Tuesday, having recovered from a 
concussion suffered Sunday. STEVE SPRINGER 
