<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The 16-year-old Saddleback College Summer Stock Company has changed its name 
to create a higher profile. It is now called the Saddleback Civic Light Opera, 
according to producer Geoffrey English. 
</P>
<P>
 English said the summer-stock program has presented more than 50 musicals for 
the past nine seasons. Although most have been Broadway revivals, they also 
have included off-Broadway shows and two original revues: "Stardust" and 
"Jumpin', Jive and Jitterbug." 
</P>
<P>
 SCLO also has announced its 1995 summer season: "Beehive" (June 10-25), billed 
as a county premiere; "Nunsense II" (July 7-23), and "Guys and Dolls" (Aug. 
4-20). 
</P>
<P>
 All three productions, with casts made up mostly of college actors and a few 
professionals, will be staged on campus at Saddleback's 400-seat McKinney 
Theatre in Mission Viejo. (714) 582-4763. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</TEXT>
