<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLACES TO TOAST THE START OF THE NEW YEAR; FESTIVITIES: HOLIDAY CELEBRATIONS 
RANGE FROM DANCING ON CATALINA TO CONCERTS AND COMEDY. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN MONIQUE FAUSTINA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Say goodby to 1994 and hello to 1995 with a variety of activities for all 
ages. Here is a list of festivities available to ring in the New Year. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County 
</P>
<P>
 Knott's Berry Farm presents "Praise '95, Jubilation," from 7 p.m. to 2 a.m. 
with Christian rock bands and fireworks at midnight. Tickets are $20 in advance 
and $22 on the day of the event. (714) 220-5200. 
</P>
<P>
 Eddie Money plays two shows at the Galaxy Concert Theatre, 3503 S. Harbor 
Blvd., Santa Ana. Tickets are $25 for the 7:30 p.m. show and $50 for the 10 
p.m. show. Available from Galaxy Theatre box office or through Ticketmaster, 
(714) 957-0600. 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Isaak at the Coach House, 33157 Camino Capistrano, San Juan Capistrano. 
Tickets for the 7 p.m. show are $25; a second show at 10 p.m. is sold out. 
Tickets available at the box office or through Ticketmaster. (714) 496-8930. 
</P>
<P>
 Comedian ventriloquist Jeff Dunham performs at the Brea Improv, 945 E. Birch 
St., Brea. There will be two seatings, at 7 and 10 p.m. Admission for the early 
show, including dinner and champagne toast, is $50, or $25 for show and toast 
only. The late show, including appetizers and unlimited champagne, is $60. All 
packages include a souvenir champagne glass and free pass to a future show. 
</P>
<P>
 Comedian Craig Shoemaker headlines at 7:30 and 10 p.m. at the Irvine Improv, 
4255 Campus Drive, Irvine. Admission for the early show, including dinner and 
champagne toast, is $40, or $20 for show and toast only. The late show, 
including appetizers and unlimited champagne, is $55. All packages include a 
souvenir champagne glass and free pass to a future show. 
</P>
<P>
 Medieval Times New Year's Eve Spectacular begins at 9:30 p.m., at Medieval 
Times Restaurant, 7662 Beach Blvd., Buena Park. Tickets are $55 and include 
buffet, sit-down feast, party favors and champagne toast at midnight. Tickets 
and reservations are available through Ticketmaster or by calling (800) 
899-6600. 
</P>
<P>
 The Orange County Crazies present "Orange Lang Syne" at the Orange County 
Crazies Theatre, 115 E. Santa Ana Blvd., Santa Ana. Refreshments at 9 p.m., 
show 10 p.m. to midnight. $25. (714) 550-9900. 
</P>
<P>
 Randell Young & the Actuals play blues at Randell's, 3 Hutton Centre Drive, 
Santa Ana, in a special package including dinner with wine, party favors, 
champagne toast and a CD. 8 p.m. $59. (714) 556-7700. 
</P>
<P>
 Ralph Dudley plays jazz for dancing at Spaghettini, 3005 Old Ranch Parkway, 
Seal Beach. Show time is 9 p.m. and there will be a complimentary champagne 
toast at midnight. Free. (310) 596-2199. 
</P>
<P>
 "First Night Fullerton" runs 7 p.m. to midnight in the streets, sidewalks, 
parking lots and buildings of downtown Fullerton. A hundred events at more than 
30 sites. The "First Night" buttons are $5 to $10. (714) 738-6545. 
</P>
<P>
 A Seniors' New Year's Eve Party will be held at the Michael E. Rodgers Senior 
Center, 1706 Orange Ave., Huntington Beach. $10. (714) 536-9387. 
</P>
<P>
 A New Year's Eve Party begins at 8:30 p.m. at the Jewish Community Center of 
Orange County, 250 E. Baker St., Costa Mesa. $60 to $70. (714) 751-0608.  
</P>
