<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOE OF ALGERIA'S MUSLIM MILITANTS SHOT DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Suspected Muslim guerrillas have shot and killed a secular opponent of Islamic 
fundamentalists in Algiers, Algerian newspapers reported Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Security forces, meanwhile, killed 16 Muslim guerrillas in ambushes and search 
operations during the last three days in five Algerian regions, the Algerian 
news agency APS said. 
</P>
<P>
 Suspected Muslim militants Saturday gunned down Belgacem Aziz, a 55-year-old 
member of the secular Ettahadi party, in Algiers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122194-0243 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 110222 </DOCID>
