<TEXT>
<P>
 Summa Industries: The Fullerton manufacturer of equipment and engineered 
industrial products reported profit of $152,000, or 10 cents a share, for the 
first fiscal quarter ended Nov. 30. That compares to profit of $231,000, or 15 
cents a share, for the like period last year, which included a gain of $100,000 
from an accounting change. Sales increased to $4 million from $3.3 million. 
