<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Selectel Corp.: A division of American Telephone & Data Inc. has won a 
contract to provide communications equipment to all rooms in the Army barracks 
at Ft.Campbell, Ky., the company said Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
 The contract, valued at $40 million, will be shared between Selectel Corp. of 
Costa Mesa, a unit of Newport Beach-based American Telephone & Data; and its 
partner on the project, AT&T Corp. By July 1, Selectel and AT&T will have 
outfitted the barracks with telephone, fax and computer lines, American 
Telephone & Data said. Selectel will oversee the installation, while AT&T will 
provide the lines and switching equipment. 
</P>
