<TEXT>
<P>
 General Automation Inc.: The Anaheim computer company reported profit of 
$427,000, or 4 cents a share, for fiscal 1994, contrasted with a net loss of 
$577,000, or 5 cents a share, for 1993.Sales for the year ended Sept. 30 
declined 19% to $34.6 million from $42.9 million. Sales and earnings in 1993 
include results of European operations that were sold effective Oct. 1, 1993. 
For the fourth quarter, the company had profit of $229,000, contrasted with a 
year-earlier loss of $1 million. Sales were down 10% to $9.4 million from $10.4 
million. 
