<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: ALPHA MICROSYSTEMS' PRESIDENT TULLIO WILL ASSUME COO 
DUTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John D. Murray will resign as chief operating officer and chief financial 
officer of Alpha Microsystems, a Santa Ana information technology products and 
services company, effective Jan. 15. The company said the resignation is 
because of medical problems in Murray's family. Douglas J. Tullio, president 
and chief executive, will assume the duties of chief operating officer. Murray 
will remain an assistant to the president on a part-time basis until the end of 
the company's fiscal year, Feb. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jeffrey W. Broker and Sean A. O'Keefe have formed the law firm of Broker & 
O'Keefe in Irvine, specializing in bankruptcy and insolvency law, workouts and 
related commercial litigation in state and federal courts. Broker and O'Keefe 
were formerly partners of Lobel, Winthrop & Broker. 
</P>
<P>
 * James L. Richter has been appointed vice president of sales and marketing 
for the commercial, industrial and medical molding groups of Cimco Inc., a 
Costa Mesa thermoplastic components manufacturer. He previously held management 
positions at General Electric and Dow Chemical companies. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thomas H. Grifferty has been named regional vice president for international 
operations at First American Title Insurance Co. in Santa Ana. Grifferty joined 
First American in 1987 as manager for Canadian operations and was appointed 
vice president for Canadian operations in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 * Anthony J. Herrera has been appointed vice president at Union Bank. He is a 
manager in the North Orange County Business Banking Center. Before joining 
Union Bank in September, Herrera was a vice president and manager for First 
Interstate Bank of California. 
</P>
<P>
 * Raymond P. Weamer has been promoted to the newly created position of vice 
president and regional sales manager for the Southwest region of Money Store 
Investment Corp. in Irvine. In his new position, he will lead a sales team of 
business development officers in the eight-state region. Previously, Weamer was 
a business development officer in the San Diego office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
